# Release v1.0 risk acceptances for dependency-only Trivy findings.
# The application does not enable Cloud Foundry actuator endpoints; health/metrics
# remain the only Compose-exposed actuator surfaces and the backend is bound to loopback.
CVE-2026-22733

# Spring Security is pinned to the latest available 5.x line that remains compatible
# with this Spring Boot 2.7 / Spring Framework 5.3 baseline. Trivy lists fixes only
# on unreleased 5.8.18 or Jakarta-based 6.x/7.x lines for this release baseline.
CVE-2026-22732
CVE-2025-22228

# Spring Boot 2.7.x has no compatible patched 2.x line. The affected actuator matcher
# and future session/predictability findings require migration to Boot 3+/4+, which is
# outside the v1.0 release scope. Production actuator exposure remains limited.
CVE-2025-22235
CVE-2026-40973

# This codebase does not expose HttpInvokerServiceExporter or Java deserialization
# remoting endpoints.
CVE-2016-1000027

# Spring Framework 5.3.x has no compatible patched 5.x release for the annotation
# detection finding; migration to Spring 6 requires Jakarta namespace changes.
CVE-2025-41249

# The backend does not use functional RouterFunctions with FileSystemResource.
# Static frontend assets are served by nginx, not Spring MVC.
CVE-2024-38816
CVE-2024-38819
